Ostriches were almost wiped out in the 18th century  
due to feather hunting. Only four of the nine original  
ostrich species still survive. Today, the widespread  
practice of ostrich farming has helped to conserve the  
remaining wild ostrich populations. The main threat  
to the ostrich now lies in the destruction of its  
natural habitat.  
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
